{
  "text": "The theme of application of specific debriefing models was found in only two papers [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . A narrative review [CITATION_3] identified nine design features in debriefing practices in education, including specific models (e.g., Debriefing With Good Judgement; Debriefing for Meaningful Learning Ó ) and more general concepts and multistep debriefing processes (e.g., Lederman's six validity discussion question; Thiagarajan's seven debriefing phases). Out of these, the Debriefing With Good Judgement method was highlighted in another paper [CITATION_4] as one of the characteristics of debriefing. [CITATION_5] suggested that the methods, models, or frameworks reflect specific debriefing processes and concluded that a variety of debriefing processes had similarities:",
